      <bioghist id="aspace_bioghist">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Born in 1875, Mary Bartlett Smith lived most of her childhood in various Massachusetts' small towns with her parents Mary and Calvin and a brother, Teddy. At Smith, she became secretary of the Current Events Club. She earned her B.A. in Classics in 1897. After graduating, she continued her education at various institutions including: Smithsonian Institute, Framingham Normal, Simmons College, Boston University, Columbia University, The Business Training Corp. of New York City, and the Chicago Bureau of Filing and Indexing. Smith taught in various private schools across New York and Massachusetts as she was completing her education, but spent most of her career as a statistician for various industries. After the death of her sister-in-law in 1936, she moved to Bartlesville, Oklahoma to help her brother raise his two sons. She died there on February 12, 1953.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_scope">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Collection contains some information about Mary Bartlett Smith's time at Smith such as photographs and some poetry published in the Smith College Weekly. However, most of the information pertains to her life as an alumna, including a large selection of her published and unpublished writings. These include a body of poetry, short stories, articles, and a memoir titled Cataracts. Mary Bartlett Smith also collected articles written by her classmate, Alice Weld Tallant '97 and which are included in the collection.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_scope-arr">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged according to genre and is arranged into eight (8) folders.</p>  
      </arrangement>
